BlackJack README

A game where the player tries to get his deck of cards to add up to 21.
Only two player:

1. The Player is issued two cards.
- One card up and one down.
2. The Dealer is issued two cards.
- One card up and one down.
3. Dealer and Player add values of cards.
- Computer calculates dealers choice of hit or bust.
- Player chooses to hit or bust.
4. If either go over 21 the other wins.
5. If both are under 21 calculate who is closest, they win.


This Blackjack design is separated into seven classes each of which are identified by their name in this directory.
